#: ../../../community/support.rst:4
msgid "Support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../community/support.rst:6
msgid ""
"If you have questions or issues about Requests, there are several options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../community/support.rst:9
msgid "Stack Overflow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../community/support.rst:11
msgid ""
"If your question does not contain sensitive (possibly proprietary) "
"information or can be properly anonymized, please ask a question on `Stack "
"Overflow <https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/python-requests>`_ and "
"use the tag ``python-requests``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../community/support.rst:18
msgid "File an Issue"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../community/support.rst:20
msgid ""
"If you notice some unexpected behaviour in Requests, or want to see support "
"for a new feature, `file an issue on GitHub <https://github.com/psf/requests/"
"issues>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../community/support.rst:26
msgid "Send a Tweet"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../community/support.rst:28
msgid ""
"If your question is less than 280 characters, feel free to send a tweet to "
"`@nateprewitt <https://twitter.com/nateprewitt>`_, `@sethmlarson <https://"
"twitter.com/sethmlarson>`_, or `@sigmavirus24 <https://twitter.com/"
"sigmavirus24>`_."
msgstr ""
